  "title": "vim/nvim not filling windows terminal",
  "body": "<p>I'm runing nvim through wsl2 on ubuntu. However if I use the windows terminal nvim or vim will not fill the whole terminal</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/O73xC.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/O73xC.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>How can I get rid of those black borders?</p>\n<p>It works just fine if I use the Ubuntu terminal. But I'd prefer to use the Windows Terminal\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/heug2.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/heug2.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n",
